Dr Arfon Williams is now the only doctor available across two rural practices in North Wales . 
  His partner and colleague of 20 years retired at the end of March . 
  Surgery has been unable to attract a replacement and is currently functioning with a skeleton service . 
  Dr Williams said he faces the challenge of providing safe care for 4,300 patients . 
  Health bosses said difficulties recruiting GPs is a national issue . 
  He said ambulances queuing at A&E is a sign the system is broken . 
 